    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently, inlay hints remain enabled when entering insert mode, as far as I am aware this behaviour cannot be configured. This causes the cursor to jump around as the type is being inferred when declaring variables, which is in my opinion annoying.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhen configured, inlay hints are automatically disabled when entering insert mode and re-enabled when insert mode is exited so that when typing code the cursor does not jump around.",
    "closed_at": "2024-05-29T11:12:51Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Just use an `InsertEnter` (and `InsertLeave`) autocommand that toggles them? Inlay hints are not enabled by default, so there is nothing to configure in this sense.",
